				Madeleine Russo is a Vice President in the Real Estate Legal & Compliance group and is based in New York.  Ms. Russo handles legal and compliance matters, focusing on Blackstone Property Partners. Prior to joining Blackstone in 2014, Ms. Russo was a Senior Associate in the Private Investment Funds group at Ropes & Gray LLP where she focused her practice on the formation and operation of private investment funds, including buyout funds, real estate funds, fund of funds, secondary funds and hedge funds.  She also worked with institutional and other investors in connection with their private fund related investments on a primary, secondary and co-investment basis.Ms. Russo received a BA in English Literature from Trinity College in Hartford, CT, with honors, and a JD cum laude from Georgetown University Law Center.
			





Luisa Santeli
Vice President
GSO
New York










Luisa Santeli
Vice President

					GSO — New York
				


				Luisa Santeli is a Vice President with GSO Capital Partners. Since joining GSO in 2007, she has been involved with providing ongoing support to the Portfolio Managers, bank debt trade settlement, cash management and loan administration. She is also involved with CLO compliance monitoring, portfolio reporting, payment distributions and mark-to-market distribution to investors. Before joining Blackstone, Ms. Santeli worked at Prudential Financial in the Fixed Income division as an Associate where she was responsible for settling European bank debt trades. Ms. Santeli received a BS in Accounting at Montclair State University.
			





Daniel Santopietro
Vice President
Finance
New York










Daniel Santopietro
Vice President

					Finance — New York
				


				Dan Santopietro is a Vice President in Strategic Partners, Blackstone’s secondary private fund of funds business, which was acquired from Credit Suisse in August 2013. Mr. Santopietro is involved in administrative, accounting, tax and financial reporting matters related to Strategic Partners’ secondary private equity funds.
Prior to joining Strategic Partners, Mr. Santopietro was a Vice President in the Asset Management Group at Credit Suisse where he was responsible for the fund administration and financial reporting of its Leveraged Buyout Private Equity Funds, Venture Capital Funds and Employee Co-Investment plans during his time with the firm.  Prior to that, Mr. Santopietro was an Associate with KPMG in their Financial Services group.
Mr. Santopietro received a BS in Accounting from the State University of New York at Albany.  He is a Certified Public Accountant in New York.
			





