Rob Walsh
Vice President

					GSO — New York
				


				Rob Walsh is a Vice President with GSO Capital Partners.  Mr. Walsh focuses on the evaluation of public and private market investments across the energy, power, metals & mining and waste sectors.Prior to joining GSO in 2013, Mr. Walsh served as an Associate within the Leveraged Finance Origination & Restructuring Group at Credit Suisse, where he focused on advising primarily corporate clients across multiple industries on high yield and leveraged loan financings.  Mr. Walsh began his career at J.P. Morgan, where he focused on various project management and internal consulting roles within the investment bank.Mr. Walsh graduated cum laude from Amherst College with a BA in history and received an MBA from the University of Virginia Darden School of Business.
			





Gabriel Wasserman
