					Real Estate — New York
				


				Gabriel Wasserman is a Vice President in the Real Estate Debt Strategies group and is based in New York.Mr. Wasserman also serves as the Controller of Blackstone Mortgage Trust (NYSE: BXMT) and is responsible for oversight of its accounting, finance and SEC reporting functions.Prior to joining Blackstone, Mr. Wasserman was a senior manager in the assurance practice at Ernst & Young where he served a diverse group of real estate entities including publicly traded REITs, private equity funds and commercial owners, operators and developers.  Mr. Wasserman received a BSBA in Accounting and Finance from Washington University in St. Louis and is a Certified Public Accountant. He is on the Board of Directors of UJA-Federation New York and The Henry Kaufmann Campgrounds.
			





