Vivian Wong
Vice President

					Real Estate — Hong Kong
				


				Vivian Wong is a Vice President in the Real Estate group and is based in Hong Kong. Since joining Blackstone in 2010, Ms. Wong has been involved with the accounting, financial reporting and fund administration, for the Special Purpose Companies of the Blackstone Real Estate Partners Funds in respect of Asia and Australia investments and for the MB Asia Fund (legacy ex-Merrill Lynch Asian Real Estate Fund). Before joining Blackstone, Ms. Wong worked for Bank of America Merrill Lynch in the Real Estate Private Equity group and was responsible for the fund administration, accounting and financial reporting for its Asia Investments. Prior to that, Ms. Wong worked for over six years in audit and business advisory in public practices in Australia. Ms. Wong received a Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting and Information Systems from the University of New South Wales in Australia. Ms. Wong is a qualified Chartered Accountant and is a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants in Australia.
			





