Band 2
第二等

Paul, Weiss, Rifkind, Wharton & Garrison LLP

Paul, Weiss, Rifkind, Wharton & Garrison LLP



View Profile
æŸ¥çœ‹ç®€ä»‹







From the Chambers USA guide

Basic facts about the departmentKey office is New York. 
What the team is known for A private equity funds practice that continues to go from strength to strength, counseling elite private equity fund managers on some of the biggest fundraisings in the market. Highly regarded for its experienced structuring of high-end formations, encompassing buyout, venture capital and mezzanine funds, among others. 
Strengths Complimentary sources remark: "They've been real partners to us. They're very business-minded and make our deals easier. A top shop." 
Interviewees find it advantageous that the team "aligns well with our goals." They also give it "high marks on responsiveness - you know you'll get a call back."
Work highlights Advised Atlas Merchant Capital regarding the formation of its $500 million financial services fund. 
